    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1918-07-15T07:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1918-07-15T07:00:00-05:00" n="221"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d221">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 763.72119/1800</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Switzerland</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_SPA1"
                        type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Stovall</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Berne</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-07-15T13:00:00+01:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">July 15, 1918, 1 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/> [<hi rend="italic">Received July 16, 8.22 p.m.</hi>]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>3958. My 3884.<note n="1" xml:id="d221fn1">
                        <hi rend="italic">Ante</hi>, <ref target="#pg_276">p. 276</ref>.</note> In
                    conversation with a member of French Embassy, latter states that <persName>De
                        Fiori</persName>, “a dangerous agent of <persName corresp="#p_LGEFW1"
                        >Ludendorff</persName>,” was in Switzerland endeavoring to get into touch
                    with Entente and especially America. It is possible that this was said to sound
                    out the Legation. Merely to avoid any misunderstanding, I shall be glad to have
                    the Department’s permission to acquaint British, French and Italian colleagues
                    with substance of <persName>De Fiori</persName>’s communications without
                    revealing channel through which received.<note n="2" xml:id="d221fn2">Answered
                        by telegram No. 2313, July 19, 5 p.m., “Department has no objection to your
                        informing British, French and Italian colleagues as you suggest.”</note>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_SPA1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Stovall</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
